A Canadian group has reported that SARS-CoV-2 has been detected in the mid-turbinate and throat swabs of a patient who had been discharged 2 weeks prior to recovery from the disease, indicating that this newly identified virus may be circulating in an influenza-like pattern.
However, there are some promising signs from China based on the declining number of new cases, which shows the positive impact of the current policies.
