First, they have a relatively high mutation rate in RNA replication.
Compared to other single-stranded RNA viruses, the estimated mutation rate of COVID is dependent on the stage of acceptance of COVID by the new host, with an average replacement rate of "mild" to "high" at -10-4 replacements per 2 sites per year.
