Based on comparative analysis between isolates of Sars-CoV and Civet, it appears that SARS-CoV has been rapidly accepted in different animals, especially with mutations in the RBD of the S protein.
Typically, in RBD in S proteins, COV interacts with the cell receptor and is actively selected by the cell's antibody response.
